    <section id="cta" class="main special">
      <h2>What is Laby?</h2>
      <p>Laby Is just a simple HTTP server : <br />
        <ul>
          <li>statically serving files in the <code>laby/www</code> folder, at <code>http://`$LABY_HOST`/antenna/api/flowers</code> </li>
          <li>Soon providing a websocket endpoint at  <code>http://`$LABY_HOST`/antenna/websocket/flowers</code> </li>
          <li>providing a REST API endpoint at  <code>http://`$LABY_HOST`/antenna/api/flowers</code>  </li>

          <ul>
            <li>Those endpoints can be customized and redeployed on-the-fly, to make what I call grope tests, a devops things</li>
            <li>I especially use it in docker environements, to determine whether the problem came from the software, from the infrastructure, or even better, from both</li>
          </ul>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </section>
